latestIgtvVideos.title: Three easy monochrome looks
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
As much as I love mixing prints and colours, wearing and playing with monochrome palettes is often a more sophisticated approach. I usually find it a quick go-to solution when I don’t have time to plan my look for a last-minute work event, meeting, or a night out. Wearing multiple layers of varied textures of  one color helps me adds depth and dimension to an outfit.
Look 1
Blazer, @zara . Pants, @zara. Earrings, @hm. Shoes, @zara.
Look 2
T-shirt, @hm. Pants, @aritzia. Scarf, @hm. Shoes, @stevemaddenindia. Earrings, @chanelofficial (vintage). Look 3
Ribbed vest top, @mango. Pants, @zara. Shoes, @zara. Necklace and earrings, @hm.

In a world chasing colour, @newbalance Grey Days asked us to pause—and feel grey. Not as absence, but presence. A hue reclaimed, redefined, and worn with pride. At their Ambience Mall, Vasant Kunj store, the brand staged more than a celebration—it was a stillness, a statement. A fashion show, a feast, a flood of sneakers—and me, dressed in a look that felt like a quiet kind of bold.

#NewBalanceIndia #GreyDays2025 #greydays

ft. @seeaash.in

A composition of rare light and line — this high jewellery choker and earrings set pairs fancy yellow diamond briolettes with white diamonds, in a silhouette that feels less worn, more remembered. Each element is placed with intention: movement, brilliance, and grace in perfect measure. Crafted by BN Jewels — a house where emotion is the blueprint and rarity is the rule. An heirloom in the making, this is more than adornment — it’s legacy.
